ğŸ Tkinter Python Snake Game

An implementation of the classic Snake Game using Python and the standard Tkinter GUI library. This project is a great way to learn about game loop mechanics, basic graphics, and event handling in Python.

ğŸŒŸ Features

Classic Gameplay: Control the snake to eat food and grow longer.

Collision Detection: Game ends upon collision with the walls or the snake's own body.

Difficulty Scaling: The snake's speed increases slightly after every food item is consumed (to a minimum speed of 50ms).

Dual Controls: Supports both Arrow Keys and WASD for movement.

Modern Aesthetics: Dark theme with vibrant color contrasts for a clean look.

âš™ï¸ Requirements

This game requires Python 3.x and the standard Tkinter library, which is typically pre-installed with most Python distributions.

ğŸš€ How to Run

Save the code: Save the provided code into a file named snake_game.py.

Run from the terminal: Open your terminal or command prompt, navigate to the directory where you saved the file, and execute:

python snake_game.py


ğŸ•¹ï¸ Controls

Key

Action

Up / W

Move snake Up

Down / S

Move snake Down

Left / A

Move snake Left

Right / D

Move snake Right

R

Restart game (on Game Over screen)

ğŸ“ Game Configuration

You can easily customize the game by changing the constants at the beginning of snake_game.py:

Constant

Description

Default Value

CANVAS_WIDTH / CANVAS_HEIGHT

Size of the game window.

600

GRID_SIZE

Size of one grid cell in pixels.

20

INITIAL_GAME_SPEED

Initial delay in milliseconds between game frames. Lower is faster.

150

SNAKE_COLOR

Color of the snake segments.

"#00cc66"

FOOD_COLOR

Color of the food item.

"#ff3333"

